Two people have died after a truck rammed into a 14 seater matatu at Kibarani Changamwe in Mombasa on Monday morning. The dawn accident left scores injured  who have been rushed to Coast General Hospital for treatment. ALSO READ:

Family of identical twins in road carnage seek answers According to witness accounts, the tanker lost control before ramming into two matatus. Changamwe OCPD Peter Onamwa said the fuel tanker had a Tanzanian registration number and was earlier trying to avoid a head on collision. More to follow.  